[size=4][u]Mimic Repeat Orders[/u][/size]

The impossible is possible: use the Mimic behavior for Repeat Orders.

[size=3][u][b]Features[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Assign any appropriate Player-owned ship to commander with [b]Repeat Orders[/b] enabled as subordinate with [b]Mimic[/b] behavior.
[*] The subordinate ship will copy the [b]Repeat Orders[/b] of its commander.
[*] Ships with insufficient AI Pilot skill to use [b]Repeat Orders[/b] will be not assigned or removed.
[*] Any changes to the commander's [b]Repeat Orders[/b] will be automatically reflected on the subordinate ship.
[*] Works with any vanilla [b]Repeat Orders[/b] order type automatically — every order parameter (search radius/position, cargo amount, price threshold, wares, etc.) is detected directly from the game engine, so new order types work without needing a mod update.
[*] Works with non-vanilla orders too, such as [b]Mining in Sector[/b] from the [b]Mining in Sector for Mimic Repeat Orders[/b] mod.
[/list]
[size=3][u][b]Limitations[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Only one level of [b]Mimic[/b] behavior is supported. Ships assigned as subordinates to subordinate ships will not be able to mimic their orders.
[*] Changes to subordinate ship's will be reflected with small delay, up to 30 seconds.
[/list]
[size=3][u][b]Specifics[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] A single [b]Repeat Orders[/b] entry is enough to enable mimicking — there is no requirement to combine multiple order types.
[/list]  So be careful, is some orders required a "pair" to work properly, like [b]Buy[/b] and [b]Sell[/b] orders for trading - there is now [b]your responsibility[/b] to manage them correctly!
[list][*] Cargo-amount parameters (e.g. the minimum/maximum amount on [b]Buy[/b]/[b]Sell[/b] orders) are automatically rescaled to match the subordinate ship's own cargo capacity, rather than copied as an absolute number — a larger or smaller subordinate ship will buy/sell proportionally more or less.
[*] If a subordinate ship cannot carry the ware used by the commander's orders, it is unassigned from the commander automatically.
[/list]
[size=3][u][b]Requirements[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]X4: Foundations[/b] 7.60 or newer (tested on 7.60 and 8.00).
[*] [b]Mod Support APIs[/b] by [url=https://next.nexusmods.com/profile/sirnukes?gameId=2659]SirNukes[/url] to be installed and enabled. Version [b]1.95[/b] and upper is required.
[list]
[*] It is available via Steam - [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2042901274]SirNukes Mod Support APIs[/url]
[*] Or via the Nexus Mods - [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/503]Mod Support APIs[/url]
[/list]
[*] [b]Options Helper[/b], to provide the in-game Debug Level option. Version [b]1.10[/b] and upper is required.
[list]
[*] It is available via Steam - [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3715253556]Options Helper[/url]
[*] Or via the Nexus Mods - [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/2089]Options Helper[/url]
[/list]
[/list]
[size=3][u][b]Installation[/b][/u][/size]

You can download the latest version via Steam client - [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3599279973]Mimic Repeat Orders[/url]
Or you can do it via the Nexus Mods - [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/1875]Mimic Repeat Orders[/url]

[size=3][u][b]Usage[/b][/u][/size]

Simple use the usual context menu options to assign a ship to commander with Repeat Orders enabled as subordinate using the [b]Mimic[/b] behavior.

